## Scope

Compute the combined-view hypervector — XOR-bind across the four populated layers (AST, Semantic, Temporal, Module). Per math-friend review F: combined view exists *only* as unweighted prefilter for top-k pruning, never as the primary index (HDC has no clean weighted bind).

## Algorithm

```rust
fn combined_hv(scope_id: &str, conn: &Connection) -> Option<Vec<u8>> {
    let layers = [LayerKind::Ast, LayerKind::Semantic, LayerKind::Temporal, LayerKind::Module];
    let mut combined = vec![0u8; D/8];
    for layer in layers {
        let layer_hv = fetch_hv(conn, scope_id, layer)?;
        let role_seed = layer_role_seed(layer);
        let permuted = role_permute(&layer_hv, role_seed);
        xor_into(&mut combined, &permuted);
    }
    Some(combined)
}
```

Triggered by:
- HdcPass run completion (recompute combined for affected scopes)
- Bulk recompute on schema migration

## Query usage

```rust
fn op_hdc_combined_prefilter(...) -> ... {
    // Stage 1: cheap top-k against combined view
    let candidates: Vec<scope_id> = sql!("SELECT scope_id FROM _hdc_combined ORDER BY popcount(hv XOR ?1) LIMIT ?2");

    // Stage 2: weighted per-layer rerank (caller owns weights)
    let rerank_sql = format!(
        "SELECT scope_id, ... FROM _hdc WHERE scope_id IN ({}) GROUP BY scope_id ORDER BY weighted_distance",
        candidates.iter().map(|_| "?").collect::<Vec<_>>().join(",")
    );
    ...
}
```

This is the cheapest path for "find similar at any layer" without paying the cost of weighted multi-table joins on the full corpus.

